sentences: Karl Willetts (born 21 September 1966) is an English death metal vocalist, best known as the lead singer of Bolt Thrower and Memoriam.
Willetts joined the British death metal band Bolt Thrower in 1988.
He stayed with Bolt Thrower until 1994, after the recording of ...For Victory.
Rumours persisted he had returned in 2001, but he did not.
However, in November 2004, he actually did re-join Bolt Thrower after the departure of Dave Ingram.
Willetts stayed in Bolt Thrower until the band broke up in 2016, following the death of drummer Martin Kearns the year before.
Willetts was a vegetarian for a long while, but started eating meat prior to 2006.
Willetts now has a degree in Cultural Studies from the Birmingham University.
